content.problemStatement:
A developer wants to change the background color and add 15 pixels of internal spacing to a box.
They write the following JavaScript code:
```js
const box = document.querySelector('#myBox');

// Option 1
box.style.backgroundColor = 'green';

// Option 2
box.style.padding = 15;

// Option 3
box.style.border-radius = '5px';
```
Which option(s) will cause an error or fail to apply the intended style?

